  "prompt": "What are your favorite YouTube channels about Star Wars content?",
  "response": "While I don't have personal preferences, I can recommend several popular YouTube channels that produce great Star Wars content:\n\n1. **Star Wars Theory** - This channel dives deep into lore, theories, and storytelling within the Star Wars universe, often exploring what-if scenarios and character analyses.\n\n2. **The Lore Master** - Focuses on the expansive lore of Star Wars, providing in-depth explanations of characters, events, and timelines.\n\n3. **Cosmic Wonder** - Covers Star Wars news, theories, and breakdowns of various aspects of the franchise, including films, series, and upcoming projects.\n\n4. **Screen Rant** - While not solely focused on Star Wars, they produce a lot of content related to the franchise, including news, discussion, and theory videos.\n\n5. **Star Wars Explained** - As the name suggests, this channel breaks down all things Star Wars, providing thorough explanations of characters, species, planets, and more.\n\n6. **The Take** - Offers analytical takes on Star Wars movies and series, exploring themes, storytelling, and character development.\n\n7. **New Rockstars** - While primarily focused on various pop culture franchises, they often cover Star Wars content with detailed breakdowns and Easter egg hunts.\n\nThese channels cater to a variety of interests, whether you're looking for lore, theories, news updates, or deeper philosophical discussions about the Star Wars saga.",
